When you have some time give me a call - at your convenience, no rush at all.

Hope you are having a great weekend.

Perfect!

I am

What’s your schedule like today? I would

Hey! Quick update. Still working. This is one of my busiest times w grant submissions. I have due dates for may 18th, 26th, june 5th and june 12th. So having to prioritize Tulane at the moment.
But in my downtime,
I am starting to do an electronic wireframe using adobe xd. Have access through Tulane. Any reason to use a different program?

I’ve used adobe XD years ago. It’s good enough. Doesn’t matter. Whatever tool you use to build and showcase user journey effectively and as long as the exercise forwards the thinking and ideas then use whatever platform you find works for you
That’s what I thought. I am really enjoying the exercise. Nice to see idea take form.

Going to send you a link to our new website created by yours truly. It’s live, but not “live”…looking to share to get feedback and your thoughts on how it conveys who we are, what we do, etc. Mind taking a look?
*this is the rebranded site.
I never got the website. I am excited to see it.
Held back just to refine some things
Will send in a bit
Thank you😊
No rush / just in case you had attached it.

Hey Steve, I scheduled a 30 min meeting for this morning at 9:30. I was hoping we could just catch up real quick. Several wonderful developments on my end.
I am totally flexible with time. I am working on a dense and very boring grant so happy for a distraction. Please let me know if you have the time today.
That works for me
Talk soon
I think it might be that your scalability perspective is skewed and still hampered by pubtrawlr thinking.I submitted the first grant today. And I have slept so available to chat.
Can I call you back tomorrow? I’m at the beach until tomorrow
No rush!
I do think I have solved some of your scalability so you might want to call me.
Let’s talk! Are you free at 9pm or tomorrow morning?
Let’s do tomorrow.
Any time work best?
Got a minute now

Time to plan not
Plans!

Then

Tomorrow
